Adam Freier previews the opening weekend of The Rugby Championship action where the Wallabies tackle the Springboks in South Africa followed by the All Blacks up against Argentina in Buenos Aires. JOHANNESBURG - Australia coach Michael Cheika on Thursday named the following team to face South Africa in their Rugby Championship test at Ellis Park on Saturday: Australia: 15-Tom Banks, 14-Dane Haylett-Petty, 13-Tevita Kuridrani, 12-Samu Kerevi, 11-Reece Hodge, 10-Bernard Foley, 9-Nic White, 8-Isi Naisarani, 7-Michael Hooper (captain), 6-Lukhan Salakaia-Loto, 5-Rory Arnold, 4-Izack Rodda, 3-Sekope Kepu, 2-Folau Fainga'a, 1-James Slipper Replacements: 16-Jordan Uelese, 17-Harry Johnson-Holmes, 18-Taniela Tupou, 19-Rob Simmons, 20-Jack Dempsey, 21-Will Genia, 22-Matt To'omua, 23-Kurtley Beale. 